{
  "stem": "18470.4",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he went to Senator Taft, who was then the-- the leading Republican congressional leader, and they got extra-maximal visas for these professors to bring them to the Cincinnati school.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Among them was Abraham Joshua Herschel and the Levys, Julius and Hildegarde Levy, who were professors of Semitic languages, truly great scholars, outstanding people.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they were the nucleus for the graduate school of the college.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "For them, Jewish scholarship was extraordinarily serious work, and they'd make great demands on us.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And that created, also, for monolingual American students, most of whom had not had serious college experience, a-- an ordeal, you know.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They demanded perfection.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, of the Wissenschaft tradition.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But they changed the climate of the school in very subtle ways.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I remember Professor Levy was-- proclaimed himself an agnostic, and yet he would, every Shabbos, he would be at the service.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And Julius Levy said no.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You come to my class.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You listen to me teach.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I come to listen to you preach.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he says, it's just a courtesy.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Now, with that, he covered the seriousness of his engagement with scholarship, with religion.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And these-- these were extraordinary people.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When I was-- I collated Nelson Glueck's inaugural lectures.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was an office boy at the New York school when I went to the evening college, and Nelson Glueck was then the president from 1947 to 1970.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was my predecessor.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yeah.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was a segregated community, which was, of course, not the case in New York.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was just reminiscing with someone yesterday who remembered me from the time when I was a student rabbi in Owensboro, Kentucky.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he was a newspaper reporter covering the integration of Lee and Sturgis, Kentucky, which were violent integrations of black kids into white schools.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
